article.headline: Saint Louis 71, Western Illinois 61
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Tommie Liddell finished with 17 points and Saint Louis scored 21 points off 23 Western Illinois turnovers to beat the Leathernecks 71-61 on Saturday. Luke Meyer added 10 points for the Billikens (6-2), who went on an 11-0 run in the second half to break the game open following a 44-44 tie. Chris Gonzalez sank all five of his field-goal attempts, including four from 3-point range, to lead Western Illinois (3-6) with 14 points. The Billikens tied the score at 29 on Kevin Lisch's two free-throws with 6.9 seconds left in the first half. It marked the fifth tie of the opening 20 minutes but quickly turned into the seventh lead change after Sammy Hunter drove the length of the court and scored on a lay-up to give the Leathernecks a 33-31 halftime lead. The sloppy game that included a total of 36 turnovers followed tough losses for both teams. Saint Louis lost by 10 at Southern Illinois on Dec. 2 and Western Illinois, playing in its fourth game during an eight-day span, lost 92-40 at Indiana on Wednesday.
